<subSubSection box="[151,394,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,429]" box="[151,394,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<heading box="[151,394,151,177]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[151,284,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Remarks on</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1888" box="[291,394,151,177]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Cardenio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Cardenio</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
As indicated in the key (couplet 1) 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1888" box="[605,710,187,213]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Cardenio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[605,710,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Cardenio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs significantly from the remaining 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1853" box="[1176,1306,187,213]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Synopiidae</taxonomicName>
. The single species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Stebbing, 1888" authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1888" box="[248,704,223,249]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Cardenio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paurodactylus">
<emphasis box="[248,521,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Cardenio paurodactylus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stebbing, T. R. R." box="[530,704,223,249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 1737" refId="ref50287" refString="Stebbing, T. R. R. (1888) Report on the Amphipoda collected by H. M. S. Challenger during the years 1873 - 76. Report on the Scientific Results of the Voyage of the H. M. S. Challenger During the Years 1873 - 1876, Zoology, 29, 1 - 1737." type="journal article" year="1888">Stebbing, 1888</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, was transferred from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1853" box="[963,1089,223,249]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Synopiidae</taxonomicName>
to a new family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barnard &amp; Karaman" authorityYear="1987" box="[1287,1436,223,249]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cardenioidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cardenioidae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Barnard, J. L. &amp; Karaman, G. S." box="[161,469,259,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="856 - 875" refId="ref48494" refString="Barnard, J. L. &amp; Karaman, G. S. (1987) Revisions in classification of gammaridean Amphipoda (Crustacea) part 3. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 100, 856 - 875." type="journal article" year="1987">Barnard &amp; Karaman, 1987</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Barnard, J. L. &amp; Karaman, G. S." box="[482,542,259,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 866" refId="ref48536" refString="Barnard, J. L. &amp; Karaman, G. S. (1991) The families and genera of marine gammaridean Amphipoda (except marine gammaroids). Records of the Australian Museum, 13 (Supplement), 1 - 866. https: // doi. org / 10.3853 / j. 0812 - 7387.13.1991.367" type="journal article" year="1991">1991</bibRefCitation>
). Jadzewski &amp; De Broyer (1990) rejected Barnard &amp; Karaman’s proposal and moved 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1888" box="[237,342,295,321]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Cardenio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[237,342,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Cardenio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
back to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1853" box="[446,576,295,321]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Synopiidae</taxonomicName>
. With a broader analysis of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1853" box="[947,1073,295,321]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Synopiidae</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1888" box="[1083,1188,295,321]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Cardenio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1083,1188,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Cardenio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may require separate family subgroup recognition for which Barnard and Karaman’s name would be available. Such a move is outside the scope of the present paper. (Jadzewski &amp; De Broyer’s (1990) paper was too late to be considered by 
<bibRefCitation author="Barnard, J. L. &amp; Karaman, G. S." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 866" refId="ref48536" refString="Barnard, J. L. &amp; Karaman, G. S. (1991) The families and genera of marine gammaridean Amphipoda (except marine gammaroids). Records of the Australian Museum, 13 (Supplement), 1 - 866. https: // doi. org / 10.3853 / j. 0812 - 7387.13.1991.367" type="journal article" year="1991">Barnard &amp; Karaman 1991</bibRefCitation>
.)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
